WEBVTT

00:00.027 --> 00:02.919
- Previously on The Resident.
- CONRAD: How's Jessie?

00:02.967 --> 00:03.966
NIC: Her kidneys are failing.

00:04.001 --> 00:06.068
So my kidneys will never work again?

00:06.104 --> 00:08.471
The drug trial did irreversible damage.

00:08.506 --> 00:10.406
(SOBBING)

00:10.442 --> 00:13.076
I will have a triple transplant
and make history.

00:13.111 --> 00:14.243
Maybe even come here as an intern.

00:14.278 --> 00:16.312
I can't think of anything more amazing.

00:16.347 --> 00:18.166
BELL: Red Rock Mountain Medical

00:18.202 --> 00:20.865
is the top health care
conglomerate in the southeast.

00:20.867 --> 00:22.000
We don't need Chastain.

00:22.035 --> 00:24.001
We will be stronger together.

00:24.036 --> 00:25.971
We have to keep fighting.

00:26.006 --> 00:28.339
The risk is pretty low for the donor.

00:28.375 --> 00:30.207
Anybody need a kidney around here?

00:30.242 --> 00:31.475
Thank you, Dad.

00:31.510 --> 00:32.844
Dad.

00:32.878 --> 00:35.347
- You're my baby girl.
- It's gonna be okay.

00:37.517 --> 00:38.932
- (ALARM BEEPING)
- (CONRAD PANTING)

00:38.966 --> 00:40.518
Where's the crash cart?!

00:40.554 --> 00:42.387
(ALARMS BEEPING)

00:42.421 --> 00:45.090
(FLATLINE)

00:49.563 --> 00:50.929
NIC: Mm.

00:50.963 --> 00:53.119
Black-eyed Susans are my favorite.

00:54.567 --> 00:56.567
Remember that time you ran away
from our family picnic?

00:56.603 --> 00:58.542
Must've been, like, four or five.

00:59.625 --> 01:01.039
Yeah.

01:01.073 --> 01:02.707
Mom and Dad were frantic,

01:02.743 --> 01:04.840
but I knew where to find you.

01:06.138 --> 01:07.436
Here.

01:09.343 --> 01:11.621
Dad was so sweet that day.

01:11.658 --> 01:14.118
He... he was crying
when he picked me up, and...

01:14.153 --> 01:17.254
I... I remember

01:17.609 --> 01:20.411
I was so happy in his arms.

01:25.966 --> 01:28.405
I keep trying to rewind the clock.

01:31.438 --> 01:34.239
There must have been something
I could have done differently.

01:34.620 --> 01:37.141
Remember what I told you, Nic?

01:42.835 --> 01:44.883
This is not your fault.

01:44.918 --> 01:47.585
(NIC SNIFFLES)

01:51.825 --> 01:53.825
CONRAD: It's getting late.

02:01.034 --> 02:02.834
It's time.

02:07.340 --> 02:09.507
We need to scatter her ashes.

02:16.716 --> 02:19.584
KYLE: Nicky, honey,
it's been almost a month.

02:19.618 --> 02:20.764
(EXHALES)

02:20.788 --> 02:22.211
I'm not ready.

