02:31.675 --> 02:35.081
♪ ♪

02:35.114 --> 02:43.117
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

02:43.143 --> 02:44.475
(INDISTINCT ANNOUNCEMENT OVER P.A.)

02:47.313 --> 02:49.280
Welcome to another rewarding day
under the heel

02:49.316 --> 02:51.983
of Red Rock Mountain Medical.

02:52.018 --> 02:54.485
(GRAVELLY VOICE): "Red Rock, Red Rock."

02:54.521 --> 02:55.819
How's Nic?

02:55.855 --> 02:59.189
UH, THE SAME: not good.

02:59.225 --> 03:01.292
We're all worried about her.

03:01.328 --> 03:02.693
We miss her.

03:02.729 --> 03:04.729
How can we help?

03:04.764 --> 03:06.965
(SIGHS) She'll be here this
morning for her dad's post-op.

03:07.000 --> 03:08.299
I'll talk to her.

03:08.335 --> 03:10.502
Sounds good.

03:10.537 --> 03:12.537
(DOOR OPENS)

03:17.711 --> 03:19.477
Where's Jonah?

03:19.513 --> 03:20.978
I took my eyes off him

03:21.014 --> 03:23.091
for two seconds and he disappeared.

03:23.127 --> 03:25.250
You know, he's probably hiding somewhere.

03:25.284 --> 03:26.550
He's afraid of needles.

03:34.227 --> 03:35.560
How much do you expect to make

03:35.594 --> 03:37.829
with this new neurosurgery center?

03:37.864 --> 03:39.764
A steady churn
of high-risk invasive brain

03:39.799 --> 03:42.432
and spine procedures generates
half a billion a year.

03:42.468 --> 03:44.401
And this new neurosurgeon
you want to have...

03:44.437 --> 03:46.103
he's a rainmaker?

03:46.139 --> 03:47.771
He was at his last hospital.

03:47.807 --> 03:49.240
He will be if he comes here.

03:49.276 --> 03:51.776
- When are you seeing him?
- Lunch today.

03:51.811 --> 03:54.945
He won't commit to Chastain
unless the two of you get along.

03:54.980 --> 03:57.382
I'll work my charm.

04:00.819 --> 04:02.453
(KYLE SIGHS)

04:05.125 --> 04:06.925
KYLE: I couldn't sleep last night,

04:06.960 --> 04:09.460
- thinking about coming back here.
- (MONITOR FLATLINING)

04:09.496 --> 04:10.861
(PANTING)

04:10.896 --> 04:12.931
(ECHOING): Come on.

04:12.966 --> 04:14.098
Jessie!

04:14.134 --> 04:15.733
(PANTING)

04:15.769 --> 04:17.569
Keep trying!

04:18.838 --> 04:20.571
You ever gonna be able
to work in this place again?

04:22.141 --> 04:23.942
I don't know.

04:23.976 --> 04:26.211
This is where Jessie was killed.

04:26.245 --> 04:28.079
No one killed Jessie, Dad.

04:28.113 --> 04:29.814
She went into surgery
with a weakened heart

04:29.848 --> 04:31.615
and died of a massive blood clot.

04:31.651 --> 04:33.918
It's a known complication
that could happen to anyone.

04:33.954 --> 04:35.786
Yeah, well,
I just want to see her records.

04:35.822 --> 04:38.790
Get another opinion
on what caused her death.

04:38.824 --> 04:40.225
Why?

04:40.259 --> 04:42.726
They did the autopsy. I saw the results.

04:42.762 --> 04:44.896
Yeah, we should just get an
expert to check it, that's all.

04:44.930 --> 04:47.665
I... We may have a case
to bring a lawsuit.

04:47.701 --> 04:49.689
Unbelievable.

04:50.336 --> 04:53.303
Always looking for an angle,
even in your daughter's death.

04:53.340 --> 04:54.572
No, I'm not looking for an angle.

04:54.608 --> 04:56.908
And this is not about money.
But somebody here

04:56.942 --> 04:59.177
- has to be held responsible.
- Jessie's gone.

04:59.211 --> 05:00.812
And she's not coming back.
There's no point

05:00.846 --> 05:02.913
in affixing blame. I mean,
I don't blame you, after all.

05:02.949 --> 05:05.315
You... Me? What? Why would you?

05:05.351 --> 05:08.019
I put my life on the line.
I donated a kidney.

05:08.053 --> 05:09.987
Eventually.

05:10.656 --> 05:12.355
It did no good.

05:13.192 --> 05:16.160
So you blame me, because...

05:16.196 --> 05:19.463
you're down a kidney
and Jessie still died.

05:19.499 --> 05:21.531
- No, I don't.
- Yeah, you do.

05:21.567 --> 05:23.367
You blame me because
I pushed for the surgery.

05:23.403 --> 05:25.302
It was her only chance.
I did everything I could

05:25.338 --> 05:27.271
- to protect her.
- Whoa, whoa, whoa. Whoa, whoa.

05:27.307 --> 05:30.341
Nic, I do not blame you.

05:30.377 --> 05:32.310
Do the post-op on your own.
I-I got to take a walk.

05:32.345 --> 05:33.978
- Oh, come on.
- (NIC SIGHS)

05:34.014 --> 05:35.480
(KYLE SIGHS)

05:54.033 --> 05:55.699
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

05:55.735 --> 05:57.334
CONRAD: Okay. Excuse me.

05:57.370 --> 05:59.336
Just one second. I'll be right back.

05:59.372 --> 06:01.738
Welcome, Eloise, to your first day

06:01.774 --> 06:03.875
as a sub-intern at Chastain.

06:03.910 --> 06:05.439
- (WHOOPS)
- (CHUCKLES)

06:05.473 --> 06:06.744
I feel like I'm dreaming.

06:06.779 --> 06:08.812
I've imagined this moment so many times.

06:08.848 --> 06:10.081
I-I can't believe it's real.

06:10.115 --> 06:11.480
Devon.

06:12.418 --> 06:14.384
- You remember Dr. Pravesh?
- Of course. Eloise.

06:14.420 --> 06:16.187
Last time I saw you, you were recovering

06:16.221 --> 06:17.922
- from a triple transplant.
- Now I'm hoping

06:17.956 --> 06:20.324
to match here, and become
a doctor at the hospital

06:20.360 --> 06:22.160
- that saved my life.
- Well, you can learn a lot

06:22.194 --> 06:24.095
from this guy. He's our top intern.

06:24.129 --> 06:26.197
And soon he'll be a second-year resident

06:26.231 --> 06:28.266
- with an intern of his own to torture.
- Oh, yeah.

06:28.300 --> 06:29.766
Oh, yeah.

06:29.802 --> 06:31.278
Don't do that.

06:31.303 --> 06:32.870
(CONRAD CHUCKLES)

06:32.906 --> 06:35.439
Now, Dr. Pravesh is gonna go over

06:35.475 --> 06:37.574
all the additional safety precautions

06:37.610 --> 06:39.009
you need to take
when you're around patients.

06:39.045 --> 06:40.244
You do know that I've been dealing

06:40.279 --> 06:41.913
with cystic fibrosis my entire life.

06:41.947 --> 06:44.548
I'm kind of an expert
in infection control here.

06:44.584 --> 06:46.012
I promise, I can take care of myself.

06:46.047 --> 06:47.124
I'll hold you to that.

06:47.159 --> 06:48.711
Dr. Hawkins, I need a hand.

06:48.747 --> 06:51.254
An eight-year-old has gone
missing. His name is Jonah.

06:55.762 --> 06:57.762
(DOOR CLOSES)

07:21.286 --> 07:24.122
♪ ♪

07:36.002 --> 07:38.002
(GAS HISSING QUIETLY)

07:40.939 --> 07:43.173
MARIE: He, uh,
he was right here in the bed

07:43.209 --> 07:44.641
and I went to get some water.

07:44.677 --> 07:46.076
Someone thinks they saw a little boy

07:46.112 --> 07:47.444
enter the stairs to the basement.

07:47.480 --> 07:48.913
I don't know why they didn't stop him,

07:48.947 --> 07:50.370
but I'm going to check.

07:54.019 --> 07:55.685
(DOOR CLOSES)

08:18.043 --> 08:19.310
Annie?

08:20.288 --> 08:22.012
Conrad. What?

08:22.048 --> 08:23.814
- (CHUCKLES) Wow.
- What?

08:25.084 --> 08:27.185
Oh, I haven't seen you since...

08:27.220 --> 08:29.319
Oh, the mountain bike race
at Stone Mountain. Right?

08:29.355 --> 08:30.822
What, two years ago? Yeah.

08:30.856 --> 08:32.789
- Oh, it's so good to see you.
- You too.

08:32.826 --> 08:34.859
So they needed another
PhD particle physicist

08:34.894 --> 08:36.461
- to fix this thing again?
- Yeah, well,

08:36.495 --> 08:38.696
you know, the plumber tried to
snake it, but you know how fussy

08:38.730 --> 08:40.730
these proton beam accelerators can be.

08:40.767 --> 08:42.899
They are fussy.

08:42.936 --> 08:44.322
Is everything all right?

08:44.356 --> 08:45.836
Came down here looking for a little boy

08:45.871 --> 08:47.238
who ran away from the ER.

08:47.273 --> 08:49.072
Oh, well, I didn't see anyone.

08:49.107 --> 08:51.056
You know what, let's check
the treatment room.

08:55.581 --> 08:57.181
(CREAKING)

08:57.216 --> 08:58.582
Hey, hey, hey, wait, I smell gas. W...

09:03.389 --> 09:05.022
(RUMBLING)

09:05.057 --> 09:06.724
What the hell was that?

09:06.759 --> 09:08.759
(ALARM BLARING)

09:10.129 --> 09:12.929
(SIREN WAILING)

09:12.966 --> 09:14.197
What happened?

09:14.234 --> 09:17.567
An explosion in the proton beam
accelerator room.

09:17.604 --> 09:19.604
(ALARM BLARING)

09:26.812 --> 09:28.745
(GROANS) Fi-Fire.

09:28.780 --> 09:30.114
Don't move.

09:30.149 --> 09:31.849
I have to find the boy.

09:31.884 --> 09:34.451
(GROANS)

09:38.290 --> 09:39.490
Jonah.

09:41.793 --> 09:42.826
Jonah.

09:49.469 --> 09:51.969
Let me go. Let me... I just...
I have to find Jonah.

09:52.004 --> 09:54.739
My baby. I... No, no, no. I have
to find him. I have to find...

09:54.774 --> 09:56.474
What's going on? Where's Conrad?

09:56.509 --> 09:57.746
He went down there.

10:01.947 --> 10:02.947
- Oh, my God.
- (DEVON COUGHS)

10:04.182 --> 10:06.182
(COUGHS)

10:13.493 --> 10:14.892
DEVON: Right here, right here.

10:14.927 --> 10:16.494
- Conrad!
- (DOOR RATTLING)

10:16.528 --> 10:18.763
Conrad, it's Nic. Open the door.

10:18.798 --> 10:21.264
Open the door.

10:21.301 --> 10:22.966
Oh, my God. You're bleeding.

10:23.001 --> 10:24.735
No, I'm okay. (EXHALES) I'm okay.

10:24.770 --> 10:26.770
- I can't get the door.
- Let me-let me try, let me try.

10:26.806 --> 10:28.505
Oh, it must have been damaged
in the explosion.

10:28.541 --> 10:29.840
It's jammed shut.

10:29.875 --> 10:31.408
Get out of the building. There's a fire.

10:31.443 --> 10:33.110
- The whole place could go up.
- We're not leaving you.

10:33.145 --> 10:34.511
Is anyone else with you?

10:34.547 --> 10:36.514
A woman and the boy,
both badly injured. Go back,

10:36.548 --> 10:37.648
get somebody to break down the door

10:37.683 --> 10:39.015
- and then get out of here.
- Go! Go!

10:39.052 --> 10:40.585
CONRAD: Nic, get out of here!

10:40.620 --> 10:42.320
- Go.
- No.

10:42.355 --> 10:43.354
Go!

10:44.190 --> 10:46.456
(COUGHS)

10:46.491 --> 10:48.658
(GROANING)

10:51.063 --> 10:52.395
(SCREAMS)

10:58.403 --> 11:00.538
(COUGHS)

11:00.572 --> 11:02.373
CONRAD: Annie. Annie!

11:02.408 --> 11:04.207
Annie. Can you crawl to the door?

11:04.243 --> 11:05.842
- Yeah. Yeah.
- Go. Go.

11:20.058 --> 11:21.892
(ALARM CONTINUES BLARING)

11:27.399 --> 11:28.732
(GRUNTS)

11:33.338 --> 11:35.239
(ANNIE COUGHS)

11:35.274 --> 11:38.042
Conrad?!

11:39.077 --> 11:40.977
Oh, my God.

11:41.014 --> 11:42.178
(ANNIE COUGHS)

11:43.915 --> 11:45.716
Wake up.

11:45.751 --> 11:48.318
You're okay.

11:48.354 --> 11:50.354
We need some help over here!

11:55.846 --> 11:57.645
Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

11:57.682 --> 11:59.782
- Hey, hey. You're safe. The fire's out.
- (GROANS)

11:59.817 --> 12:02.817
There was a gas leak,
but they capped it off.

12:02.854 --> 12:04.658
Where are Annie and Jonah?

12:04.692 --> 12:06.462
They're both alive
and they're being treated now.

12:06.499 --> 12:08.591
Dr. Hawkins, I'll strap you down

12:08.625 --> 12:09.692
- if I have to.
- (GROANS)

12:09.726 --> 12:10.793
NIC: You were exposed to a lot of smoke

12:10.827 --> 12:12.794
and the blast may have caused
other injuries.

12:12.830 --> 12:14.996
- You have any pain?
- All over.

12:16.200 --> 12:17.499
(GROANS)

12:17.534 --> 12:18.886
- (PANTING)
- He may have a fractured rib.

12:18.928 --> 12:21.169
(GROANS) My left ankle's killing me.

12:21.205 --> 12:22.370
(EXHALES)

12:22.405 --> 12:23.938
It's really swollen.

12:23.975 --> 12:25.687
(GROANS, PANTS)

12:27.144 --> 12:29.144
Add it to the list of imaging we need.

12:29.179 --> 12:30.278
Okay.

12:30.313 --> 12:31.379
(GRUNTS)

12:35.886 --> 12:38.620
- KIT: Pupils equal and reactive.
- Have we scared you off

12:38.655 --> 12:40.922
- your first day?
- Are you kidding? I'm good.

12:40.956 --> 12:43.959
Eloise, the ER is no place for
a triple transplant survivor.

12:43.995 --> 12:46.794
I'm gowned, gloved, masked,
safe as everyone else.

12:46.831 --> 12:48.893
Please, let's focus on the patient.

12:49.834 --> 12:52.422
My neck... it hurts.

12:52.775 --> 12:54.842
- We need to maintain his C-spine.
- We got you, buddy.

12:54.868 --> 12:56.900
I know it's hard.
Try not to move your head.

12:56.926 --> 12:58.392
Airway intact.
Breath sounds clear bilaterally.

12:58.417 --> 13:00.417
We should put him on high-flow
oxygen in case of possible

13:00.442 --> 13:02.075
- carbon monoxide exposure.
- Good call.

13:02.100 --> 13:03.899
Let's get him in a face mask.
Make sure to send

13:03.924 --> 13:05.957
- a carboxyhemoglobin level.
- DEVON: Eloise, help me out.

13:05.982 --> 13:08.384
- How's he looking?
- Minor injuries and burns.

13:08.885 --> 13:10.952
But I'm concerned about his C-spine.

13:14.544 --> 13:18.245
Jonah, can you squeeze my finger?

13:23.134 --> 13:25.234
KIT: Possible spinal cord injury.

13:25.269 --> 13:26.911
Let's get him to CT now.

13:26.946 --> 13:28.903
DEVON: All right. Let's go.

13:30.908 --> 13:32.640
(MONITORS BEEPING RAPIDLY)

13:34.077 --> 13:36.445
BP 60/40, tachy in the 140s.

13:36.480 --> 13:39.014
- She's crashing.
- Bolus a liter LR

13:39.048 --> 13:40.115
and get blood ready for transfusion.

13:40.150 --> 13:41.517
No breath sounds on the left.

13:41.552 --> 13:43.315
- Trachea deviated on the right.
- AUSTIN: Tension pneumo.

13:43.350 --> 13:44.586
The shrapnel must've pierced her lung.

13:44.621 --> 13:46.221
- Chest tube kit.
- No time.

13:46.256 --> 13:47.894
Scalpel.

13:56.600 --> 13:57.966
(MONITOR BEEPING)

13:58.001 --> 13:59.033
IRVING: Sats are coming up,

13:59.068 --> 14:00.438
but her pressure's still tanking.

14:00.474 --> 14:03.504
Irving, chest tube. Okafor, ultrasound.

14:11.922 --> 14:13.288
Abdomen is filled with fluid.

14:13.312 --> 14:14.500
- She's hemorrhaging.
- AUSTIN: Damn shrapnel.

14:14.557 --> 14:15.956
She's not stable for CT.

14:15.993 --> 14:17.892
Let's take her to OR. Now.

14:23.332 --> 14:25.899
- Where are you taking her?
- OR Two.

14:29.806 --> 14:31.706
Hey, can you finish this?

14:31.741 --> 14:33.107
Thanks.

14:34.945 --> 14:36.110
Nic.

14:36.145 --> 14:37.745
What the hell... Are you all right?

14:37.780 --> 14:39.913
- I'm fine.
- What about Conrad?

14:39.950 --> 14:42.616
He's banged up pretty bad,
but he'll be okay.

14:42.653 --> 14:44.119
Thank God.
The other two weren't so lucky.

14:44.153 --> 14:45.486
What can I do to help?

14:45.522 --> 14:47.422
Nothing. Just go home. Take the keys.

14:47.456 --> 14:48.956
- Nic, come on. Hey.
- I'm gonna stay with him.

14:48.991 --> 14:51.326
Nic, Nic. Nic.

14:54.264 --> 14:55.963
MINA: Shrapnel everywhere.

14:55.999 --> 14:57.966
This woman has saved a lot of lives.

14:58.000 --> 14:59.668
It's time we save hers.

14:59.702 --> 15:00.668
I'll take the chest.

15:00.703 --> 15:02.259
You got the abdomen.

15:02.860 --> 15:04.172
Here, sit down.

15:04.206 --> 15:06.607
Yes, ma'am.

15:11.780 --> 15:15.081
I did triathlons with Annie.

15:15.351 --> 15:18.186
I saw her once give up the lead
in a race just to help someone

15:18.211 --> 15:20.879
who took a fall.

15:21.957 --> 15:23.792
That's Annie.

15:23.826 --> 15:26.566
Does she have any family
that we need to notify?

15:26.601 --> 15:27.761
I'm not sure.

15:27.798 --> 15:29.264
I know she got a divorce.

15:29.298 --> 15:30.664
And then, not long after that,

15:30.701 --> 15:33.033
her son died in a car accident.

15:33.070 --> 15:34.302
(EXHALES)

15:34.336 --> 15:36.543
God, that's awful.

15:39.042 --> 15:40.378
MINA: Just ran the bowel.

15:40.413 --> 15:42.258
No obvious injuries.

15:42.812 --> 15:44.178
Shrapnel by the abdominal wall.

15:44.213 --> 15:46.514
Well, I took out three
from the chest wall.

15:46.549 --> 15:49.683
The last one I see is there.

15:49.720 --> 15:52.011
Lodged into the aortic arch and
abutting the pulmonary artery.

15:52.048 --> 15:54.621
- Of course.
- We pull this out, she might blow.

15:54.658 --> 15:56.224
She might blow if we don't pull it out.

15:56.259 --> 15:58.158
Well, she won't, because
you know what to do, right?

15:58.195 --> 15:59.394
Yes, I do.

15:59.428 --> 16:03.130
I'll clamp the proximal and distal aorta

16:03.166 --> 16:05.988
and control the PA
with vessel loop, just in case.

16:06.024 --> 16:09.053
Nice job. And pull on three.

16:09.090 --> 16:11.472
One, two,

16:11.508 --> 16:14.341
three.

16:14.376 --> 16:16.024
(MONITORS BEEPING)

16:16.059 --> 16:17.979
CHU: Pressure's dropping fast.

16:18.014 --> 16:19.514
AUSTIN: All right, we got this, Chu.

16:19.548 --> 16:20.815
Just buy us some more time.

16:20.850 --> 16:22.350
We're maxed on pressors.

16:22.384 --> 16:24.552
(MONITOR ALARM BEEPING)

16:29.625 --> 16:31.326
All right.

16:31.360 --> 16:34.226
We are... done.

16:36.298 --> 16:37.599
Look at that.

16:39.302 --> 16:40.869
- CHU: Pressure's coming back.
- (AUSTIN CHUCKLES)

16:40.903 --> 16:42.059
Of course it is.

16:42.085 --> 16:43.370
(LAUGHS)

16:43.405 --> 16:44.773
I love this game.

16:44.807 --> 16:46.206
Wonder Twins do it again.

16:46.243 --> 16:47.375
(MINA CHUCKLES)

16:47.409 --> 16:48.777
AUSTIN: 5-0 Prolene.

16:48.812 --> 16:50.577
- (EXHALES)
- Hey, what's going on?

16:50.614 --> 16:52.547
I'm, uh...

16:52.581 --> 16:54.615
faking a fainting spell
to get your attention.

16:54.650 --> 16:56.216
Come on, lie down.

16:56.253 --> 16:57.751
- (GROANS)
- Careful.

16:57.788 --> 16:59.888
I told you it was too soon
to get off that gurney.

16:59.923 --> 17:01.255
(GROANS) I just...

17:01.291 --> 17:03.224
I just need some fluids.

17:03.259 --> 17:04.459
- I'm light-headed.
- Okay.

17:04.492 --> 17:06.693
- I'll get you an IV.
- No, don't.

17:06.730 --> 17:09.063
(EXHALES)

17:09.098 --> 17:10.964
Stay with me.

17:12.501 --> 17:14.935
(QUIETLY): Okay.

17:22.511 --> 17:25.579
When I saw you lying
on the ground I thought...

17:27.935 --> 17:29.936
I was so scared.

17:32.242 --> 17:34.288
I'm not going anywhere.

17:35.416 --> 17:37.084
You're stuck with me.

17:40.497 --> 17:42.630
(SIGHS)

17:42.665 --> 17:44.932
I love you.

17:44.968 --> 17:47.167
I love you, too.

17:53.276 --> 17:56.477
I've only seen this one time
before in my entire career.

17:56.512 --> 17:59.012
Occipital-cervical dislocation.

17:59.048 --> 18:00.248
What does that mean?

18:00.282 --> 18:02.115
Internal decapitation.

18:02.152 --> 18:05.519
It's when the spinal column is
separated from the skull base.

18:05.555 --> 18:07.872
The blast from the explosion
must have done this.

18:07.906 --> 18:09.790
Well, the patient you saw before...

18:11.228 --> 18:12.626
...did they make it?

18:12.662 --> 18:13.862
No.

18:13.896 --> 18:15.296
Most don't.

18:17.046 --> 18:18.511
Let's get him to the OR.

18:28.637 --> 18:31.271
SSEPs and MEPs on.

18:31.307 --> 18:34.275
Fusing C1 and C2.

18:34.310 --> 18:35.643
- (MONITOR BUZZES)
- (SIGHS)

18:35.679 --> 18:36.677
Blast.

18:37.794 --> 18:39.268
Again.

18:41.217 --> 18:42.517
(MONITOR BUZZES)

18:43.146 --> 18:44.519
It's the cord.

18:44.554 --> 18:46.397
Gonna have to perform
a laminectomy to give

18:46.433 --> 18:48.355
the cord more room, then fuse.

18:48.391 --> 18:51.125
Doesn't that mean
he could end up a quadriplegic?

18:51.161 --> 18:53.394
Not if I can help it. Rongeurs.

18:54.364 --> 18:55.970
O'NEIL: What are you still doing here?

18:56.005 --> 18:57.644
You're supposed to be meeting Dr. Cain.

18:57.644 --> 18:59.777
Two of today's patients
are still critical.

18:59.811 --> 19:01.711
And they're being taken care of.

19:01.748 --> 19:03.416
You're not needed here.

19:06.385 --> 19:09.185
Dr. Cain is not a man you keep waiting.

19:09.221 --> 19:11.288
- (SCOFFS)
- Do you know how much he bills?

19:11.324 --> 19:12.289
Uh...

19:12.325 --> 19:14.959
$80 million a year.

19:15.994 --> 19:17.193
80...

19:17.663 --> 19:18.862
million.

19:19.683 --> 19:21.464
I want you to focus on that number.

19:21.500 --> 19:23.756
- (BEEPING)
- (KIT EXHALES)

19:23.790 --> 19:25.903
- Got it. (EXHALES) Oh!
- (CHUCKLING)

19:25.939 --> 19:27.201
Oh.

19:27.227 --> 19:28.739
(SIGHS)

19:28.775 --> 19:32.276
Kit Voss just reattached that boy's head.

19:32.311 --> 19:35.313
If she'd been off
by a fraction of a millimeter,

19:35.347 --> 19:37.315
an eight-year-old
would be paralyzed for life.

19:37.349 --> 19:38.442
Or dead.

19:38.479 --> 19:41.152
Dr. Voss bills two million a year.

19:41.186 --> 19:42.319
Cain is our future.

19:42.355 --> 19:44.087
Voss is our past.

19:45.290 --> 19:47.991
I can't guarantee
her contract will be renewed.

19:48.027 --> 19:50.260
(INHALES SHARPLY)

19:50.296 --> 19:51.828
What we need

19:51.864 --> 19:54.865
is more doctors like that.

19:56.802 --> 19:59.103
♪ I pray ♪

19:59.137 --> 20:02.138
♪ I pray it's not too late... ♪

20:03.977 --> 20:04.942
Ah.

20:04.978 --> 20:06.876
Thank you.

20:13.385 --> 20:16.586
♪ Wading in the wa... ♪

20:16.622 --> 20:18.455
♪ You know I love it ♪

20:18.490 --> 20:19.890
Dr. Cain.

20:21.661 --> 20:23.527
- Call me Barrett.
- Randolph.

20:23.563 --> 20:26.297
It's an interesting hobby you got here.

20:26.332 --> 20:28.965
Yeah, it's outsider art,
all from Georgia.

20:29.001 --> 20:31.134
Wherever I live, I try to immerse myself

20:31.170 --> 20:32.635
in the local culture.

20:32.672 --> 20:35.306
Can I get you both some champagne?

20:35.340 --> 20:36.374
No.

20:36.409 --> 20:38.209
That would be lovely.

20:38.243 --> 20:40.044
Yes, please do.

20:40.078 --> 20:41.711
(BELL CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

20:42.749 --> 20:45.148
Are we the only ones here?

20:45.183 --> 20:48.088
- Show's not open yet.
- Oh.

20:48.125 --> 20:49.720
They offered me a preview.
I don't know...

20:49.756 --> 20:51.188
probably thought I was more likely to buy

20:51.223 --> 20:52.834
if I had first pick.

20:52.869 --> 20:54.959
They were right. (BOTH CHUCKLE)

20:54.993 --> 20:56.460
Hey, I'm sorry I'm late.

20:56.496 --> 20:58.443
We had a bit of an emergency
this morning.

20:58.479 --> 20:59.730
Yeah, I heard about that. Is it true

20:59.766 --> 21:03.366
that the proton beam therapy
facility is a total loss?

21:03.403 --> 21:05.469
Yeah.

21:05.505 --> 21:07.971
$220 million investment destroyed.

21:08.007 --> 21:09.373
If I didn't know better,

21:09.409 --> 21:11.041
I'd think Red Rock blew it up themselves.

21:11.076 --> 21:13.911
(CHUCKLES) I was thinking
the same exact thing.

21:13.945 --> 21:17.333
Proton beam therapy facilities...
they lose millions annually.

21:17.367 --> 21:18.848
Well, when Chastain built it,

21:18.884 --> 21:22.185
they had profit projections
way north of reality.

21:22.221 --> 21:23.721
How far north?

21:23.756 --> 21:26.022
- The arctic circle.
- (CHUCKLES)

21:26.058 --> 21:29.492
And now Red Rock walks away
with a big insurance payout.

21:29.528 --> 21:32.262
Where I grew up,
they call that insure and burn.

21:32.298 --> 21:34.230
Or a stroke of good luck.

21:34.267 --> 21:37.801
Except, of course, for the two
people who nearly died.

21:42.741 --> 21:45.442
See anything that tempts you, Dr. Cain?

21:47.212 --> 21:48.546
Most definitely.

21:49.749 --> 21:51.248
I'll take that one.

21:51.284 --> 21:52.782
Great choice.

21:52.818 --> 21:55.286
I'll get the paperwork going.

21:55.320 --> 21:57.822
This is gonna double its value
in five years.

21:59.157 --> 22:01.192
And if it doesn't, is it still art?

22:01.227 --> 22:03.727
Oh, it will. It will.

22:03.762 --> 22:06.096
Lunch at the Provence Grill?

22:08.101 --> 22:10.567
- On Red Rock Mountain Medical.
- Oh, well, in that case,

22:10.603 --> 22:13.104
I'll have the oysters and...
more champagne.

22:13.138 --> 22:15.005
(CHUCKLES)

22:22.913 --> 22:24.513
Thank you.

22:28.019 --> 22:30.287
I want to go check on Annie.

22:30.323 --> 22:31.989
Okay, let's go.

22:32.023 --> 22:34.752
Uh, Mina wants to talk to you.

22:35.361 --> 22:37.694
I'll be fine. I won't do anything crazy.

22:38.763 --> 22:41.050
I'll come find you.

22:48.473 --> 22:49.778
How's he doing?

22:49.804 --> 22:50.974
(SIGHS)

22:51.009 --> 22:53.911
The ankle's gonna be an issue
for a while, but...

22:53.945 --> 22:56.346
(SIGHS)

22:56.382 --> 22:58.414
...I'm just so glad he's okay.

22:58.451 --> 23:00.416
Mm.

23:00.452 --> 23:02.452
And how are you?

23:03.935 --> 23:05.903
We've all been worried.

23:08.369 --> 23:09.993
You're probably the one person I know

23:10.028 --> 23:12.028
who understands how I feel.

23:16.982 --> 23:18.950
Does it ever get any easier?

23:21.406 --> 23:23.840
I wish I could promise you it would.

23:25.310 --> 23:27.310
(SNIFFLES, SIGHS)

23:30.316 --> 23:31.882
Walk with me.

23:33.177 --> 23:35.344
(MOUTHS)

23:41.738 --> 23:43.270
When my sisters died,

23:43.306 --> 23:46.441
I could hardly get out of bed
for two years.

23:46.476 --> 23:48.476
I do not want that to happen to you.

23:52.080 --> 23:53.748
Every day, I wake up,

23:53.782 --> 23:55.817
and the first thing I think
is she's not here.

23:58.288 --> 24:00.506
And she's never gonna be here again.

24:02.892 --> 24:04.525
It's like there's a hole in your heart

24:04.560 --> 24:05.926
that you'll never fill.

24:09.332 --> 24:10.932
(SNIFFLES)

24:10.967 --> 24:13.768
My whole life, I had one job.

24:13.803 --> 24:15.036
Take care of Jessie.

24:15.070 --> 24:17.305
Okay, that was not your only job.

24:17.339 --> 24:19.207
You take care of so many people.

24:19.241 --> 24:21.709
I know, I know. My patients need me.

24:21.743 --> 24:23.211
No, I was not gonna say that.

24:23.246 --> 24:25.913
What I was gonna say is that you...

24:26.328 --> 24:28.295
you need your patients.

24:30.019 --> 24:32.052
Work, Nic,

24:32.087 --> 24:34.588
is the only way out of grief.

24:35.625 --> 24:37.625
(BABY CRYING)

24:39.127 --> 24:41.628
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

24:42.548 --> 24:44.173
See the mother and child?

24:46.368 --> 24:48.368
Think something's wrong.

24:49.506 --> 24:51.172
- NIC: Hey.
- WOMAN: I know.

24:51.207 --> 24:53.461
- You okay?
- Um...

24:53.496 --> 24:56.243
It's my baby. She's been sick,
coughing and wheezing.

24:56.278 --> 24:57.944
Well, let's get her in to see a doctor.

24:57.980 --> 24:59.614
No. The last time I went into an ER,

24:59.648 --> 25:01.281
it cost me $6,000.

25:01.317 --> 25:02.750
The hospital sued me when I couldn't pay,

25:02.785 --> 25:04.085
and now they're docking it
from my paycheck.

25:04.119 --> 25:05.653
We can't live off what we have left.

25:05.688 --> 25:07.020
I came here to have her seen

25:07.056 --> 25:08.422
in the free clinic, but it was closed.

25:08.458 --> 25:10.159
That's horrible.

25:11.394 --> 25:14.663
So I've been waiting out here,
hoping Diana would get better.

25:16.566 --> 25:19.165
She's wheezing badly.
We need to get her in there now.

25:19.201 --> 25:20.800
Oh, it's okay.

25:20.836 --> 25:22.403
- Come on.
- NIC: Come on.

25:26.049 --> 25:27.607
Surgery was successful.

25:27.644 --> 25:30.044
We're certain we got all the shrapnel.

25:30.304 --> 25:31.846
CONRAD: How do you feel?

25:31.881 --> 25:34.413
Like I just got split in half.

25:34.448 --> 25:35.938
How are you doing?

25:35.972 --> 25:37.951
That's typical Annie Diamonte.

25:37.987 --> 25:39.487
Worried about everybody but yourself.

25:39.521 --> 25:40.635
(SCOFFS)

25:40.661 --> 25:42.123
I got a few bruises.

25:42.157 --> 25:45.226
Small fracture of an ankle bone,
but it won't even need surgery.

25:45.260 --> 25:47.119
We should stop talking.

25:47.154 --> 25:49.155
You need your rest.

25:49.805 --> 25:53.201
In the injury Olympics,
you solidly got me beat.

25:55.003 --> 25:56.971
When can I go home,

25:57.006 --> 26:00.040
Dr. Hawkins, do you think?

26:00.076 --> 26:03.711
I'd rather not stay here
any longer than I have to.

26:04.881 --> 26:08.348
What... like, what, a week or two?

26:11.520 --> 26:13.587
(CRYING)

26:13.623 --> 26:17.023
Temperature's 102.5.

26:17.059 --> 26:19.359
(MONITORS BEEPING)

26:19.394 --> 26:21.194
- Sats are back up in the 90s.
- Is she okay?

26:21.230 --> 26:22.696
She has bilateral wheezes

26:22.731 --> 26:24.865
and is using accessory muscles.
Likely an infection.

26:24.901 --> 26:27.835
Labs are back.
Viral swab is positive for RSV.

26:27.869 --> 26:30.171
Everyone put on a mask and gown.

26:30.205 --> 26:32.000
DEVON: Eloise,

26:32.036 --> 26:33.740
RSV is extremely dangerous

26:33.776 --> 26:35.175
for people who have had
a lung transplant.

26:35.211 --> 26:37.893
I'm aware. I'm gloved.
I'm gowned. I have a mask.

26:37.927 --> 26:39.498
Can you all please stop coddling me

26:39.532 --> 26:40.748
and treat me like any other sub-I?

26:40.782 --> 26:42.349
No, because you aren't any other sub-I.

26:42.384 --> 26:44.218
This has gone on long enough.

26:44.252 --> 26:46.119
Please leave.

26:46.154 --> 26:47.887
Now.

26:47.923 --> 26:49.913
DEVON: Dr. Feldman's right.

26:49.949 --> 26:51.791
I'll come find you when I'm done here.

26:56.231 --> 26:59.066
Right lower lobe infiltrate,
and her white blood cell count

26:59.102 --> 27:00.266
and procalcitonin are up.

27:00.290 --> 27:02.303
I'm afraid she might have
developed a bacterial pneumonia.

27:02.337 --> 27:04.137
Oh, God, I'm so sorry. What did I do?

27:04.173 --> 27:05.306
DEVON: Even with continuous nebs,

27:05.340 --> 27:06.973
her respiratory rate is still in the 40s.

27:07.009 --> 27:08.096
We might need to intubate.

27:08.121 --> 27:10.443
Let's get her
on IV ceftriaxone and azithro,

27:10.480 --> 27:12.113
and let's get her to the PICU now.

27:12.147 --> 27:13.713
What?

27:13.750 --> 27:15.583
(CRYING CONTINUES)

27:17.869 --> 27:21.588
So, it looks like RSV
plus a bacterial pneumonia.

27:21.624 --> 27:23.990
Probably strep,
if I were to put my money on it.

27:24.027 --> 27:25.925
The most common bacterial pathogen

27:25.961 --> 27:27.666
- in children her age.
- Not bad.

27:27.701 --> 27:29.313
You know your stuff.

27:29.347 --> 27:31.464
My expertise in infection control

27:31.500 --> 27:34.434
is only surpassed
by my encyclopedic knowledge

27:34.470 --> 27:36.737
- of lung disease.
- Cystic fibrosis will do that.

27:36.772 --> 27:38.765
ELOISE: Sure will.

27:40.343 --> 27:43.477
Some of your antirejection meds
will cause that tremor.

27:43.512 --> 27:44.979
Goes away over time.

27:45.521 --> 27:47.356
Shouldn't be a problem by intern year.

27:48.317 --> 27:51.152
Look, I'm sorry that Dr. Feldman
was harsh back there,

27:51.186 --> 27:52.952
but it is our job to keep you safe.

27:52.989 --> 27:55.155
This is my body and my life.

27:55.191 --> 27:57.646
I'm not anybody's kid to protect.

27:57.682 --> 27:59.859
Safety isn't my main priority.

27:59.895 --> 28:02.163
I go white water rafting
every chance I get.

28:02.198 --> 28:03.698
I even go skydiving.

28:03.732 --> 28:04.999
You're not scared?

28:05.034 --> 28:06.534
Course I'm scared.

28:06.568 --> 28:09.103
Every time I cough,
I think about rejection.

28:09.137 --> 28:12.138
But I want to live, and that means risk.

28:12.174 --> 28:14.375
What you all need to remember is

28:14.410 --> 28:17.545
I'm a doctor in training now,
not your patient.

28:29.325 --> 28:31.224
I couldn't understand
what was going on in the ER.

28:31.259 --> 28:32.559
What's wrong?

28:32.595 --> 28:34.295
I promise you she's in great hands.

28:34.329 --> 28:36.163
She has RSV and bacterial pneumonia.

28:36.199 --> 28:38.531
She needs oxygen, antibiotics

28:38.567 --> 28:41.969
- and fluids.
- I can't believe I let it get this bad.

28:42.003 --> 28:43.837
- If only I...
- It's not your fault.

28:43.873 --> 28:46.740
You were put in an impossible situation.

28:46.776 --> 28:49.042
The system is broken.

28:50.880 --> 28:51.878
Yeah.

28:51.913 --> 28:53.247
- You the mom?
- Yeah.

28:53.281 --> 28:54.582
You can come in now.

28:54.616 --> 28:56.217
She's doing better.

28:56.634 --> 28:57.951
Thank you.

29:04.192 --> 29:07.193
Hmm. If the clinic were still open,

29:07.230 --> 29:09.298
we could have treated her daughter

29:09.334 --> 29:11.415
with antibiotics and avoided all of this.

29:11.451 --> 29:12.700
Red Rock cut the funding.

29:12.734 --> 29:14.335
You can't run a clinic without money.

29:14.369 --> 29:18.198
Mm-hmm. But if you came back,
we could find the money.

29:19.075 --> 29:21.075
One way or another.

29:21.109 --> 29:23.277
I can't do it alone,

29:23.311 --> 29:26.913
but we can together, Nic.

29:32.555 --> 29:34.454
CONRAD: Yeah, it's palinopsia.

29:34.490 --> 29:36.123
She's continuing to see something

29:36.159 --> 29:37.625
after it's no longer there.

29:38.844 --> 29:40.971
Very common after head trauma.

29:43.839 --> 29:46.096
Don't tell me we got this woman
through a fire,

29:46.121 --> 29:48.858
an explosion
and a life-threatening injury

29:48.884 --> 29:51.022
only to find out she has a brain tumor.

29:55.644 --> 30:00.038
♪ ♪

30:14.513 --> 30:16.160
NIC: I just heard.

30:16.194 --> 30:18.328
Annie has a brain tumor?

30:18.354 --> 30:19.835
(SIGHS)

30:19.835 --> 30:21.101
I'm so sorry.

30:21.135 --> 30:22.568
How bad is it?

30:22.604 --> 30:26.272
Well, she has
a posterior cortical lesion,

30:26.307 --> 30:28.575
a small hemorrhagic component and edema.

30:28.609 --> 30:30.777
That accounts for her new symptoms.

30:30.811 --> 30:33.445
No signs of cancer anywhere else. Yet.

30:33.481 --> 30:35.848
So it might not be metastatic.

30:37.184 --> 30:38.484
The radiologist couldn't be certain.

30:38.519 --> 30:40.487
We need to see the pathology report.

30:40.521 --> 30:42.192
Cain is certain he can remove all of it.

30:42.227 --> 30:44.037
AUSTIN: What? He can't know that

30:44.073 --> 30:45.911
until he's actually in there.

30:59.807 --> 31:01.807
PUND: Dibs.

31:03.111 --> 31:05.077
JESSICA: Would you like me to start

31:05.113 --> 31:06.613
your playlist, Dr. Cain?

31:06.647 --> 31:08.347
You know it.

31:08.383 --> 31:11.817
("OLD TOWN ROAD (REMIX)"
by Lil Nas X playing)

31:11.853 --> 31:13.653
(SCOFFS)

31:13.689 --> 31:16.489
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh... ♪

31:17.526 --> 31:21.193
Texas born and bred.

31:21.229 --> 31:23.770
♪ Yeah, I'm gonna take my horse ♪

31:23.807 --> 31:25.587
♪ To the old town road ♪

31:25.623 --> 31:29.001
♪ I'm gonna ride
till I can't no more... ♪

31:29.037 --> 31:31.003
Probe.

31:31.038 --> 31:32.471
♪ To the old town road ♪

31:32.507 --> 31:33.873
- ♪ I'm gonna ride ♪
- ♪ Kio ♪

31:33.909 --> 31:36.209
- ♪ Till I can't no more ♪
- ♪ Kio ♪

31:36.243 --> 31:38.345
♪ I got the horses in the back ♪

31:38.380 --> 31:39.979
♪ Horse tack is attached ♪

31:40.015 --> 31:41.747
♪ Hat is matte black ♪

31:41.782 --> 31:43.958
♪ Got the boots that's black to match ♪

31:43.992 --> 31:45.684
♪ Ridin' on a horse, ha ♪

31:45.721 --> 31:47.119
